Bring a #large pot{} of water with a large pinch of @salt{} to a boil. Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Remove and thinly slice the @Swiss chard{8%oz} stems; thinly slice the leaves. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced).

Add the Swiss chard stems to the boiling water and cook for ~{2%minutes}, until tender. Add the Swiss chard leaves and cook for another ~{1%minute}, until wilted. Remove with a #slotted spoon{} and set aside. Leave the water boiling on the stove—we'll be using it later!

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add the onion and cook, tossing, for ~{5-6%minutes}, until softened. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

While the onions cook, add the @penne pasta{6%oz} to the boiling water and cook for ~{9-10%minutes}, until al dente. Reserve ¼ cup pasta water then drain.

Add the @mixed wild mushrooms{4%oz} and another drizzle of olive oil to the pan with the onions and cook, tossing, for about ~{5%minutes}, until golden brown. Season with salt and pepper. Add the garlic, @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, and as many @chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like (start with a little and go up from there!).

Add the @sour cream{4%oz} and ¼ cup pasta water to the pan. Stir to combine and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}, until slightly thickened.

Add the drained penne, Swiss chard, and half the @Parmesan cheese{1%oz} to the pan and toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper. Serve the penne with the remaining Parmesan and enjoy!